			<div type="leaf">
				<p>
					<pb facs="#f008"/>
					<metamark facs="#f008_z000" function="folio" n="9" place="top right" rend="pencil">9</metamark>
				</p>
				<p>altogether tell. Certain it is, however, that<lb/> this great power of blackness in him derives<lb/> its force from its appeals to that Calvinistic<lb/> sense of <del change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z001" hand="#HM" rend="overwritten">innate</del> <add change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z001" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="overwritten">Innate</add> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z002" hand="#HM" rend="overwritten">depravity</del> <add change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z002" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="overwritten">Depravity</add> and original Sin, from whose<lb/> visitations, in some shape or other, no deeply thinking<lb/> mind is always &amp; wholly free. <add change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z004" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">For, in</add><metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z003" function="caret" place="inline" rend="guideline">^</metamark> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z005" hand="#HM" rend="strikethrough">In</del> certain moods,<lb/> no man can weigh this world, without throwing<lb/> in something, <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z008" function="caret" place="inline" rend="guideline">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z009" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">somehow</add> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z010" hand="#HM" rend="strikethrough"><restore>like</restore></del> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z011" hand="#HM" rend="overwritten">original</del> <add change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z011" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="overwritten">Original</add> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z012" hand="#HM" rend="overwritten">sin</del> <add change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z012" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="overwritten">Sin</add>, to strike the<lb/> uneven balance. At all events, perhaps no<lb/> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z006" hand="#HM" rend="strikethrough">author</del> <add change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z007" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="no-caret">writer</add> has ever <add change="#StB" facs="#f008_z014" hand="#ESM" place="inline" rend="fill-in-blank">wielded</add> this terrific thought with<lb/>greater <add change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z015" hand="#ESM" place="inline" rend="fill-in-blank">terror</add> than this same harmless<lb/> Hawthorne. Still more: this black <add change="#StB" facs="#f008_z016" hand="#ESM" place="inline" rend="fill-in-blank">conceit pervades him,</add><lb/> through &amp; through. You may be witched by his<lb/> sunlight,-- transported by the bright gildings<lb/> in the skies he builds over you;-- but there is<lb/> the blackness of darkness beyond; and even <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z018" function="caret" place="inline" rend="caret">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z019" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">his</add> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z017" hand="#HM" rend="strikethrough">these</del> <lb/><del change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z020" hand="#ESM" rend="strikethrough">light</del> <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z021" function="caret" place="inline" rend="caret">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z022" hand="#ESM" place="above" rend="caret">bright</add> gildings but fringe, and play upon the<lb/> edges of thunder-clouds<add change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z023" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no-caret">.</add>--  In one word, the<lb/> world is mistaken in this Nathaniel Hawthorne.<lb/> He himself must often have smiled at its<lb/> absurd misconception<del change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z024" hand="#HM" rend="overwritten">.</del> <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z024" function="caret" place="inline" rend="guideline">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z025" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">of him.</add> He is immeasurably deeper<lb/> than the plummet of the mere critic. For it<lb/> is not the <add change="#StB" facs="#f008_z031" hand="#ESM" place="inline" rend="fill-in-blank">brain</add> that can test such a man;<lb/> it is only the heart. You cannot come to<lb/> know greatness by <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z027" function="caret" place="inline" rend="guideline">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z028" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="caret">inspecting it;</add> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z026" hand="#HM" rend="strikethrough">much pondering;</del> there is no<lb/> glimpse to be caught of it, except by intuition;<lb/> you <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z029" function="caret" place="inline" rend="caret">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z030" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">need not</add> ring it, you but touch it, and you find<lb/> it is gold</p>
				<p>     now <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z032" function="caret" place="inline" rend="caret">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z033" hand="#ESM" place="above" rend="caret">it is</add> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z034" hand="#HM" rend="strikethrough">this</del> <add change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z035" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="no-caret">that</add> blackness in Hawthorne, of<lb/> which I have spoken, that so fixes &amp; fascinates<lb/> me. It may be<add change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z036" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no-caret">,</add> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z036" hand="#HM" rend="multi-stroke">however</del> <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z037" function="caret" place="inline" rend="guideline">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f008_z038" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">nevertheless,</add> that it is too</p>
			</div>
